This paper discusses the concept of Adversarial Resilience Learning (ARL) for modeling and training artificial neural networks as competitive agents in complex systems. The paper focuses on the application of ARL in detecting attack vectors in power systems, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning techniques such as actor-based testing and neural networks (cs.LG, cs.NE) to implement ARL. Finally, the paper also discusses the application of ARL in complex systems (cs.SY), further supporting the likelihood of these sub-categories.
